# Interaction Layers

People interact with ToonFi at different levels.
None of them are required.

---

## Just Looking Around

This includes:
- Browsing characters
- Viewing labs or experiments
- Reading logs or descriptions
- Watching things slowly change

No interaction required.

---

## Clicking & Unlocking

Light interaction like:
- Clicking buttons
- Unlocking pages or tools
- Spending small amounts of coins
- Voting or encouraging outcomes

This is where ToonFi usually starts to feel alive.

---

## Playing Games

Some parts of ToonFi include:
- Short arcade-style interactions
- Skill or timing-based challenges
- Resource earning through storytelling

Interactions are meant to be quick and replayable.

---

## Owning Things

Ownership-based interaction includes:
- NFTs that unlock context or access
- Items that evolve over time
- Carrying progress across experiences

Ownership doesnâ€™t mean obligation.
It just changes what you can see or do.
